21/03/2011
ATHENS, Greece -- Police announced on Sunday (March 20th) the arrests of five Greeks and one Albanian citizen and the seizing of 2.5 tonnes of marijuana, one of the biggest stashes ever intercepted in the country. 
The action was part of a months-long operation to bust an international drug smuggling group. 
The drugs, loaded in a truck, were seized near the central town of Larissa. 
Police say the drugs originated in Albania and were bound for London drug market. 
(Radio Free Europe, Capital.gr, Inews - 20/03/11)
